            <p><emph rend="italics">The Jewish Exponent.</emph><lb/>
                PUBLISHED EVERY FRIDAY.<lb/>
                929 FILBERT STREET.<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia&#44; April 4th&#44; 1890.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir&#58;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>We bet to call your attention to the trust fund recently estab&#45;<lb/>lished by Baron de Hirsch&#44; and the purposes&#44; as outlined in the en&#45;<lb/>closed&#44; which appeared in THE JEWISH EXPONENT of April 30 4th&#44; to which<lb/> this large income is to be annually devoted.<lb/></p>
            <p>The administration of this trust affects large interests in<lb/> which the entire American&#45;Jewish community is concerned&#44; and a public<lb/> discussion of the questions involved cannot but Prove of great value<lb/> in arriving at a proper solution.  We request&#44; therefore&#44; a clear<lb/> expression of your views on the following points&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>1. What are the best methods of dealing with the Russian&#45;Jewish<lb/> immigrants to America&#44; and what the end thereby to be attained&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>2. What has been the development of the Russian&#45;Jewish immi&#45;<lb/>grants in your vicinity&#44; and what the greatest need for improving<lb/> their condition and the condition of future arrivals&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>3. Within the lines marked out by the deed of trust&#44; in what<lb/> way can the Baron de Hirsch trust fund be expended to the best ad&#45;<lb/>vantage&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>4. What dangers&#44; if any&#44; are threatened by reason of immigra&#45;<lb/>tion&#44; and are to be kept in view in the administration of the trust&#44;<lb/> and how are they to be avoided&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>5. What will be the probably results derived from the trust&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>Awaiting your early response&#44; I remain&#44;<lb/> Very truly yours&#44;<lb/> CHARLES HOFFMAN&#44; Editor.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
